The content of the subject involves students' individual work under supervisor's guidance in obtaining necessary skills for writing their master's theses as well as preparing written papers related to the master's theses. 
During the course, students will report on their research results in academic presentations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  In-depth developing of master students' skills at carrying out academic research work and writing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completing the subject, master students: - will acquire skills of systematic cooperation with their supervisor; - will draw up a research plan for a semester and be able to critically analyze its fulfillment; - will associate theoretical standpoints of their research topics with appropriate methods of analysis and the empirical material to be analyzed in their research work; - will implement necessary methods for an analysis of the empirical material in academic writing, proceeding from the topic of their research work ; - will acknowledge basic principles of academic writing and be able to apply them in compiling master's theses; - will be able to express in a well-reasoned manner fundamental positions of their research topic in an academic presentation.
